&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An opportunity has arisen with the Applications, Development and Support Team for a Development Specialist to assist with the design, development and maintenance of the Trust’s applications and software solutions. As a team, we are expanding our use of the Microsoft Office 365 Power Platform (e.g. PowerApps, Automate etc.) as well as Robotic Process Automation (RPA) and would like you to play a key role in this.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As a Development Specialist you will be motivated, dynamic and have an exceptional eye for detail. It is essential that you are a team player and have excellent interpersonal and communication skills. The successful candidate will need to have a keen interest in software development with knowledge in one or more of the following: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;ASP.NET Web forms, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;SQL, integration and the Power Platform; but further specialised training will be provided.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: James Richardson&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title:  Development Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address:  james.richardson3@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
